---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
<section class="hero">
  <h1>Building scalable systems,<br>one module at a time.</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Software Architect | Advocate for Module Federation & Rspack Ecosystem</p>
    <p class="description">
    I transform complex web systems into interconnected, scalable and maintainable ecosystems - Always sharing insights and my experiences from building distributed systems and modern web applications.
  </p>
  <div class="cta-buttons">
    <a href="/blog" class="btn btn-primary">Read My Writing</a>
    <a href="https://github.com/YanPes" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View GitHub</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Recent Articles</h2>
  <div class="blog-preview">
    <article class="article-card">
      <div class="article-meta">January 2026 · 8 min read</div>
      <h3>Module Federation in Practice: Lessons from Production</h3>
      <p class="article-excerpt">
        After implementing module federation across multiple teams, I've learned what works 
        and what doesn't. Here are the patterns that emerged from real-world usage.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>

<style>
.hero {
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.hero .subtitle {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.25rem);
  color: var(--accent);
  font-weight: 400;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.hero .description {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  max-width: 600px;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

.cta-buttons {
  display: flex;
  gap: var(--spacing-sm);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  font-family: var(--font-main);
}

.btn {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
  text-decoration: none;
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 700;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  border: 1px solid var(--accent);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  position: relative;
}

.btn-primary {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--accent);
  box-shadow: none;
}

.btn-primary:hover {
  background-color: var(--accent);
  color: var(--bg-primary);
  box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(192, 254, 4, 0.4);
}

.btn-primary::before {
  content: "> ";
}

.btn-secondary {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  border-color: var(--border-color);
}

.btn-secondary:hover {
  border-color: var(--text-primary);
  color: var(--text-primary);
  box-shadow: none;
}


.blog-preview {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-md);
}

.article-card {
  text-decoration: none;
  color: inherit;
  display: block;
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
  padding-left: var(--spacing-lg);
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  background: transparent;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  position: relative;
}

.article-card:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
  padding-left: calc(var(--spacing-lg) + 10px);
}

.article-card:last-child {
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}

.article-card:last-child:hover {
  border-left-color: var(--accent);
}

.article-meta {
  font-family: var(--font-main);
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
}

.article-card h3 {
  transition: color 0.2s ease;
  margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
  color: var(--text-primary);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.article-card h3::before {
  content: ">";
  margin-right: 10px;
  color: var(--accent);
  opacity: 0;
  transform: translateX(-10px);
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.article-card:hover h3::before {
  opacity: 1;
  transform: translateX(0);
}

.article-card:hover h3 {
  color: var(--accent);
}

.article-excerpt {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.about-grid {
  display: grid;
  gap: var(--spacing-lg);
}

.bio {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .hero {
    padding: var(--spacing-md) 0;
  }

  .cta-buttons {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .btn {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
    min-width: 140px;
  }
}
</style>
